          h1.divide-section Nav
          p.info Defines different styles for list navigations.
          h2 Usage
          p
            | To apply this component, add the 
            code .nav
            |  class to an 
            code= "<ul>"
            |  element. Use 
            code= "<a>"
            |  elements as menu items within the list. To apply an active state to a menu item, just add the 
            code .active
            |  class.
          h3.tm-article-subtitle Example
          .width-medium-1-3
            ul.nav.nav-side
              li.active
                a(href='#') Active
              li
                a(href='#') Item
              li
                a(href='#') Item
          p
            span.badge.badge-info NOTE
            | By default, the nav has no styling. That's why it is important to add a modifier class to give it some styling. In our examples we used the
            code .nav-side
            | class.
          h3.tm-article-subtitle Markup
          pre.
            
          hr.article-divider
          h3 Nested navs
          p
            | You can easily add any number of
            code= "<ul>"
            | elements to your nav.
          
          table.table.rounded
            thead
              tr
                th Class
                th Description
            tbody
              tr
                td
                  code .nav-sub
                td
                  | Add this class to the first nested
                  code= "<ul>"
                  | for optimized spacing.
              tr
                td
                  code .parent
                td Add this class to indicate a parent menu item.
              tr
                td
                  code .nav-parent-icon
                td Add this class to the nav to add icons, indicating parent items.
          

          h4.tm-article-subtitle Example
          .width-medium-1-3
